            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The correlator will be set up in dual polarization mode, centered at ~260GHz with 4 spectral windows defined to simultaneously measure HCN and multiple lines of CH3OH.  The observed species are listed in Table 1. Each window will have a spectral resolution of ~0.3 km/s in order to spectrally resolve the ~2 km/s linewidths associated with these objects.
We have chosen a setting, with spectral averaging, that will sufficiently cover the lines of interest at a spectral resolution needed to determine velocity structure within the coma from jets or other physical effects.  
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our observations can be conducted in configurations from C36-1 to C36-5, and representative sensitivity calculations were done using the C36-2 beam size
of 0.8''. The maximum angular scale of ~5'' is comparable to the extended source structure observed for H2CO in other comets (see science justification).  We understand the more extended configuration will resolve out larger scale structure, and complimentary observations at single dish facilities should compensate as previously done for comet Lovejoy. 

</prj:justificationText>
